      "role": "user",
      "content": "But isn't there a difference between \"evolution\" and total replacement? A lot of people feel that once you reach a certain tipping point where the traditional majority is no longer the dominant cultural force, the old institutions basically stop functioning the way they were intended. When a culture changes that fundamentally and so quickly, doesn't it make it almost inevitable that the existing social order will collapse under the weight of competing, incompatible values?",
