      "content": "It is accurate that the speed and magnitude of demographic shifts can challenge institutions originally designed for majority rule, raising legitimate fears about the legitimacy and functionality of current political frameworks. However, historical precedents from other long-standing democracies suggest that institutional adaptation, rather than collapse, is the more common outcome when societies prioritize negotiation over crisis. The preservation of social order often depends more on the inclusive design of political institutions than on the maintenance of a purely homogeneous cultural majority.",
